cat_description: From their fosterer: Bella and Clara are the sweetest bonded sisters. They are about 6 months old and were rescued off the streets. They’ve come so far since they were rescued and show every day how much they love being indoor kitties. These sisters love curling up together on a sunny couch or in their bed. They also love playing with wand toys, wrestling down the hall and exploring every inch of the apartment. Bella is a purr machine and adored attention. She can’t get enough morning pets, night time snuggles and really any opportunity to hang. Clara’s love language is quieter, but once you swaddle her in a blanket or towel, know she’s in her happy place. She lives for some behind the ear scratches. Together they are quite a special pair.Bella and Clara let us clip their nails with no problems and aren’t into scratching surfaces other than their scratch pads. After their time on the street, they really don’t like outside noise, so a quiet home is important for them. Two low-maintenance kitties with so much love to give!

cat_description: From his rescuer: Meet Biscotti–also known as Scottie, Bisco, and cutie 💜 He’s had a playful, impish sparkle in his eye since day one, and I’ve known ever since that he was destined for indoor life 🥰Once he gets past a lil nervousness (transitioning indoors from day-to-day outdoor survival is huge!), Biscotti becomes a sweet, cuddly little mush who will curl up in your lap for hours <3 All it takes is a few words of love and patience from you (and maybe some Churus lol) ✨Biscotti is just a young man but he is already very accomplished–he can make two kinds of biscuits (air and blanket) and uses the litterbox like a pro! A chatterbox, he has a lot to say and will love to chat with you ❤️ (A staccato “Meow-meow?” is one of his favorite questions 😍)TBH I’m jealous of whoever gets to help this little cuddle monster fully settle into indoor life! He’s totally delightful and full of personality, fun, and love–he’d probably benefit from having a nice cat friend to play with and learn from too ☺️Please pick (intake) appointment when scheduling!
full_html:

From his rescuer: Meet Biscotti–also known as Scottie, Bisco, and cutie 💜 He’s had a playful, impish sparkle in his eye since day one, and I’ve known ever since that he was destined for indoor life 🥰

Once he gets past a lil nervousness (transitioning indoors from day-to-day outdoor survival is huge!), Biscotti becomes a sweet, cuddly little mush who will curl up in your lap for hours <3 All it takes is a few words of love and patience from you (and maybe some Churus lol) ✨

Biscotti is just a young man but he is already very accomplished–he can make two kinds of biscuits (air and blanket) and uses the litterbox like a pro!

A chatterbox, he has a lot to say and will love to chat with you ❤️ (A staccato “Meow-meow?” is one of his favorite questions 😍)

TBH I’m jealous of whoever gets to help this little cuddle monster fully settle into indoor life! He’s totally delightful and full of personality, fun, and love–he’d probably benefit from having a nice cat friend to play with and learn from too ☺️

Please pick (intake) appointment when scheduling!

cat_description: From her fosterer: Castle is the sweetest friend to have around the house. She might be a little slow to warm up to you at first, but once you have won her loyalty, this tabby won’t be afraid to follow you around, nudge, and nuzzle you. She will greet you at the door when you come home each day and will meow when she’s hungry or when she wants you to wake up and give her attention. She goes absolutely crazy for chicken treats and will climb onto your lap for one. Castle is independent, explorative, and confident, and a sweet household companion who takes great interest in all that her humans do. She does have some kidney issues, which are currently stable but requires a special food – which, luckily, she loves. ** Select Foster Pick Up (Cafe) when scheduling****

cat_description: Say hello to Earthquake and Firestorm! This bonded pair is full of energy and eager to exploreanything and everything around them! They love to play hide and seek with each other andcuddle on top of each other for hours on end. Earthquake (the brown tabby) sometimes can’tseem to get close enough to you (yes, he loves to spoon) and he will definitely let you know heis enjoying your company and belly rubs with his sweet purrs. The pair love to find entertainmentaround the house including watching reality TV alongside you. Firestorm (the black and whiteone) is the less confident one of the pair, but her more outgoing and chill brother is showing herthat she can trust humans more and more everyday. They both love to play and eat Churus allday long. These two special kitties have truly come out of their shell during their time in a fosterand will continue to do so in their next spot!** Select Foster Pick Up (Cafe) when scheduling****

cat_description: Nicholas is a charming, social man-about-town. His ruggedly handsome demeanor and bigcheeks will lure you in for cuddles, and he never fails to love you back.Spotted eating garbage on the side of the road, he came running as soon as we opened a can of real cat food. Obviously friendly, Nicholas had been living on the streets for a while, always strategizing his next meal and making friends along the way.This easy going boy is a lover not a fighter, gets along with other cats, and is searching for a stable forever home. This little guy deserves a family who will commit to him forever, having struggled for several years on the street.

cat_description: This pair seems super special! They are adorable and as they are from the same yard we think they'd like to stay together for good. From their caretaker:Widdie is the best! She was rescued from a backyard in Brooklyn and her former temporarybed was lined with newspapers, the front page of which had an article about Spencer Dinwiddiefrom the Brooklyn Nets in all caps. She happened to be sitting on the ‘din’ when it was decidedwe needed to name her. Widdie has stuck ever since. She loves people, is very trusting, andmore wonover by attention than food. Her appetite from curiosity is also very present in herpersonality, a character who wants to know and learn. She loves to cuddle and be pet in yourlap. She loves to hunt a feather toy, or any toy for that matter. Her favorite spaces are in ornear windows and don’t forget to acknowledge her everytime you see her - its her favorite thing!Beau loves to be around people and will be all in with a lounge or a chill session. He is also food obsessed, you can really excite him with treats or a can of food! We think this is why he has a scruffy nose because when he was found outdoors he was always too hungry to realize he would push his whole face in the bowl! His favorite toy is a dancing string but he’s known to play-attack his own tail and roll around happily.  If he’s not entertaining himself, he’s usually lounging about waiting for the next mealtime.  He’s a very gentle and calm young man!***please pick (intake) option when scheduling pick up!
full_html:
Widdle & Bo

3 year old pair

Ready now, rescuer can meet you at the cafe

This pair seems super special! They are adorable and as they are from the same yard we think they'd like to stay together for good. From their caretaker:

Widdie is the best! She was rescued from a backyard in Brooklyn and her former temporary
bed was lined with newspapers, the front page of which had an article about Spencer Dinwiddie
from the Brooklyn Nets in all caps. She happened to be sitting on the ‘din’ when it was decided
we needed to name her. Widdie has stuck ever since. She loves people, is very trusting, and
more wonover by attention than food. Her appetite from curiosity is also very present in her
personality, a character who wants to know and learn. She loves to cuddle and be pet in your
lap. She loves to hunt a feather toy, or any toy for that matter. Her favorite spaces are in or
near windows and don’t forget to acknowledge her everytime you see her - its her favorite thing!

Beau loves to be around people and will be all in with a lounge or a chill session. He is also food obsessed, you can really excite him with treats or a can of food! We think this is why he has a scruffy nose because when he was found outdoors he was always too hungry to realize he would push his whole face in the bowl! His favorite toy is a dancing string but he’s known to play-attack his own tail and roll around happily. If he’s not entertaining himself, he’s usually lounging about waiting for the next mealtime. He’s a very gentle and calm young man!

***please pick (intake) option when scheduling pick up!
